::: ex-title
Predicting probability of late stage breast cancer diagnosis
:::
::: ex-cont
For someone 60 years old, what is the predicted probability for late stage breast cancer diagnosis (with confidence intervals)?
:::
:::

**Needed steps:**

1. Calculate probability prediction
2. Check if we can use Normal approximation
3. Calculate confidence interval

    a.   **Option 1:** Using logit scale then convert to probability scale (can use even if Normal approximation criteria not met)
    b.   **Option 2:** Using Normal approximation directly on probability scale

4. Interpret results

## Example: Late stage breast cancer diagnosis

::: example
::: ex-title
